              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "ACCEL"
                ],
                "institute": "2GERMUN"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " AMS setup in Munich Maier-Leibnitz Lab.",
                " based on 14 MV tandem accelerator.Combination of large",
                "accelerator and dedicated particle detection system",
                "featuring a time-of-flight system, a gas-filled magnet",
                "and multi-anode ionization chamber fulfills the",
                "requirement of sensitive Ni-59 detection."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Ti-T target was bombarded with 1.2 and 2.6 MeV",
                " deuterons to produce 17 and 19 MeV neutrons."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " 17-MeV neutron fluence (1.48 +-0.07)*10**12 n/cm**2,",
                "  irradiation time 4 days.",
                " 19-MeV neutron fluence (1.38+-0.06)*10**12 n/cm**2,",
                "  irradiation time 8 days."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Ni samples served in previous experiment as fluence",
                "monitor,when irradiating Al samples for the measurement",
                "of Al-27(n,2n) Al-26 cross sections at 17 and 19 MeV",
                " ( see REL-REF A.Wallner,T,,2000 ).",
                "Natural Ni samples with a thickness of 0.125 mm, 10 mm",
                "diameter. Distance between neutron-producing target",
                "and Ni foil 14 mm. Positioned at 0 deg relative to",
                "incoming d+ beam."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Time history of relative flux monitored with",
                "scintillation counter positioned under 108 deg relative",
                "incoming d+ beam in distance of about 3 m."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 122 keV gamma-line was measured with HP-Ge-diode",
                " to determine the activity of irradiated Ni samples.",
                " Self absorption of photons in Ni foil was negligible."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PSD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Pulse shape discrimination for neutron-gamma",
                " discrimination.",
                " Production of Ni-59 via (n,gamma) on Ni-58 from",
                " thermalized neutrons was negligible."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "  Activation technique combined with"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "AMS"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "    accelerator mass spectrometry.",
                " Four independent AMS measurement were performed.",
                " Standard samples (produced via irradiation of natural",
                " nickel powder with thermal neutrons) served as",
                " reference material for the final isotope ratios.",
                "Isotope ratio was calculated from activity measurements",
                "relative using thermal neutron cross section of Ni-64,",
                "sig-gamma=1.52+-0.03 b, and taking into account thermal",
                "cross section of Ni-58 , sig-gamma=4.13+-0.05 b.",
                "Ni-59/Ni isotope ratio of standard material was",
                "determined to (9.1+-0.4)*10**-11 ."
              ]
            }
          ],
